format of the files:
- every field is represented by a sequence of characters. 
- First is a number, which signifies the initial state
- Then a sequence of letters signifies separate layers. RGB/rgb are automatically translated to colours, but anything can be used. Capital letters are considered walls.
- X,Y signify the initial player position


controls:
- weadzx movement of X
- WEADZX movement of Y
- 0-9 specify how many fields behind the player should change
- i - toggles restricted mode - this mode switches only the fields in radius which are of the colour from which the player has moved
- s quit
